description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for motivated nurses with a keen interest in cardiology to join our dynamic, friendly team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous experience in cardiology is by no means essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We will provide training and development opportunities, and have many&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;cardiac specialist nurses who support the team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ward 4 is a 24 bedded newly refurbished ward providing care for a large range of cardiology patients including, heart failure, MI, pre/post angiogram/plasty, endocarditis, cardiomyopathy and out of hospital cardiac arrest.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ysbyty Glan Clwyd is the regional centre in North Wales providing the services for primary PCI.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is opportunity to rotate and work in other areas within cardiology.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Come and join this ever changing exciting speciality.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Part time and full time hours are available.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal visits are very much welcomed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Campbell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager 01745534246&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Webster&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputy Ward Manager 01745534246&lt;/p&gt;
